* Q: When was my serial# "xx631xx" MacPlus made?<BR>
A: The important digits to 
figure out are the 3rd, 4th and 5th. The 3rd<BR>
digit is the last digit of the year 
(will be 5 through 9 or 0), in this<BR>
case 6 is for 1986. The 4th and 5th are the 
week of the year (will be 01<BR>
through 52), in this case the 31st week of the 
year. So yours was made the<BR>
first week of July, 1986.<BR>
